Sentencas: La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 (LSCF) nanopowders, which are being investigated as a promising cathode material for low-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (SOFCs), were synthesized by citric acid gel combustion method.
Titulo: Synthesis of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Nanopowders and Their Application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The LSCF nanopowders synthesized at 700 degrees C are single perovskite phases and have an average particle size of less than 30 nm.
Titulo: Synthesis of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Nanopowders and Their Application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: In order to evaluate the use of the synthesized LSCF nanopowders as cathode material of low-temperature SOFCs, anode-supported SOFCs were fabricated from the synthesized LSCF nanopowders and tested in the conditions of humidified hydrogen for anode and oxygen for cathode.
Titulo: Synthesis of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Nanopowders and Their Application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The anode-supported single cell with the LSCF cathode sintered at 700 degrees C showed high electrical performance with the maximum power density of 771 mW cm(-2) at 600 degrees C.
Titulo: Synthesis of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Nanopowders and Their Application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells

Sentencas: The results show that the synthesized LSCF nanopowders are suitable to be applied as cathode material for low-temperature SOFCs.
Titulo: Synthesis of La0.8Sr0.2Co0.8Fe0.2O3 Nanopowders and Their Application in Solid Oxide Fuel Cells
